      <facts>
        <reasoning>This passage documents a major escalation: the previously foreshadowed hostile-plant faction launches a full, coordinated assault on the facility, producing sustained structural damage and casualties, and Florence (previously isolated) returns and successfully imposes a tactical approach that changes the defenders from chaotic reaction to coordinated defense. Significant long-term facts: the attack actually occurred and inflicted real damage and injuries (Runner, Remedy, Velvet; facility structural damage); hostile forces use specific tactics (spore clouds, projectile thorns, corrosive vines, coordinated underground networks); Florence's tactical competence is proven and the group adopts her ‘contract-to-core’ strategy under duress; Buddy contributes usable tactical tracking data. These facts matter later for resources, morale, trust dynamics, repair/rehab timelines, and strategic posture toward hostile plants. There are no contradictions with previously established facts—the passage develops and confirms earlier foreshadowing (hostile plants intended to attack, Florence’s conditional aid, Buddy’s tracking ability) rather than contradicting them.</reasoning>
        <established>
          <fact id="CHANGE_HOSTILE_PLANTS_ATTACK_BEGINS">The hostile-plant faction initiated a coordinated, multi-directional assault on the facility, breaching walls and attacking from above, laterally, and underground.</fact>
          <fact id="CHANGE_FACILITY_SUSTAINS_MAJOR_DAMAGE">The facility sustained major structural damage during the assault (multiple wall breaches, sections of ceiling collapsed, floor destabilized, pervasive structural failure threatening core systems).</fact>
          <fact id="CHANGE_RUNNER_INJURED_DURING_ATTACK">Runner was injured in the underground fighting (vines torn, leaking sap) and continues to engage despite wounds.</fact>
          <fact id="CHANGE_REMEDY_INJURED_AND_CHEMICAL_RESERVES_LOW">Remedy was struck by falling debris and is injured; Remedy's chemical/defensive reagent reserves are becoming depleted during the engagement.</fact>
          <fact id="CHANGE_VELVET_DAMAGED_AND_CONTRACTS_PERIMETER">Velvet sustained damage from spore attacks and corrosion; on Florence's orders Velvet contracted its defensive barrier inward to form a tighter perimeter protecting the facility core and essential systems.</fact>
          <fact id="CHANGE_FLORENCE_REENTERED_COMMON_AREA_AND_OFFERED_TACTICS">Florence returned to the common area (ending her prior isolation) and offered tactical guidance during the attack, positioning herself as the tactical coordinator on her mobile platform.</fact>
          <fact id="CHANGE_FLORENCE_PROVIDES_EFFECTIVE_TACTICAL_COMMAND">Florence's tactical directives (abandon outer defenses, concentrate on the core, target load-bearing roots, coordinate Remedy/Runner/Velvet actions) materially improved the defenders' coordination and turned the situation from chaotic defense to a working, strategic posture.</fact>
          <fact id="CHANGE_DEFENSE_STRATEGY_CONTRACT_TO_CORE_PRIORITIZE_LIFE_SUPPORT_MEDICAL_AND_KIRA">The defenders adopted a deliberate strategy to abandon indefensible outer areas and concentrate defense on a contracted inner perimeter protecting life support, medical equipment, and Kira; this prioritization guided subsequent actions.</fact>
          <fact id="CHANGE_HOSTILE_PLANT_TACTICS_DEFINED">Hostile plants employed combined tactics including airborne spore clouds (toxin), projectile thorns, corrosive/decaying creeping vines that dissolve defenders, and a coordinated underground root network to destabilize foundations.</fact>
          <fact id="CHANGE_BUDDY_PROVIDES_REALTIME_TACTICAL_TRACKING">Buddy actively provided real-time tactical tracking (identifying multiple distinct hostile masses, underground groups, trajectories) and relayed that data to defenders and to Florence, becoming a useful part of coordination.</fact>
          <fact id="CHANGE_DEFENDERS_BEGIN_HOLDING_UNDER_COORDINATION">After adopting Florence's tactics and using Buddy's tracking, the facility defenders began to hold against coordinated assaults (repelling coordinated pushes and stabilizing key breaches), though the facility remained badly damaged and resources strained.</fact>
